It leverages the semantic article tag (which denotes each tweet), and the data-testid='tweet' attribute, which is specifically and consistently used on tweet containers. This approach avoids unstable or auto-generated classes/IDs, captures all cards of the described type—even as the DOM changes or classes are regenerated—and is confirmed to match the correct multiple tweet cards (including those with images). This matches the 'multiple' cardinality, as expected for a list.
